INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','page',0,5,5,'und',0,'FAQS placeholder','','filtered_html'),('node','webform',0,6,6,'und',0,'Contact us','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,13,13,'und',0,'<p>Loving Support Makes Breastfeeding Work© is the United States Department of Agriculture’s (USDA)&nbsp;national breastfeeding promotion and support&nbsp;campaign. Education, training and outreach materials are provided for&nbsp;staff of the&nbsp;Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants and Children&nbsp;(WIC).&nbsp;Resources are also available for women and their families/friends and health care providers/community partners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Key Messages:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Helping women feel comfortable with breastfeeding</li>\r\n	<li>Tips on how breastfeeding can work around a busy schedule</li>\r\n	<li>The involvement of family and friends to make breastfeeding a success</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Campaign Goals:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increase breastfeeding initiation rates among WIC participants</li>\r\n	<li>Increase breastfeeding duration among WIC participants</li>\r\n	<li>Increase referrals to WIC for breastfeeding support</li>\r\n	<li>Increase general public acceptance and support of breastfeeding</li>\r\n	<li>Provide support and technical assistance to WIC State and local agencies in the promotion of breastfeeding Key Messages</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,24,24,'und',0,'<p>Learning how to breastfeed takes time <em>and </em>patience. Here are some frequent questions <em>new </em>mothers have about breastfeeding.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,25,25,'und',0,'<p>Most people think of breastfeeding as something just between mom and baby. The truth is, breastfeeding is a special time for everyone. Breastfeeding gives mom, dad, grandparents and the entire family a reason to be proud and become part of the new baby’s life.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,26,26,'und',0,'<p>Many new mothers worry about breastfeeding around others, even around people they know. With a little planning and practice, they soon find they can breastfeed anytime, anywhere. And you will too.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,27,27,'und',0,'<p>Juggling work, school, family, friends, or other demands might make you nervous about breastfeeding or wonder if it’s worth it if you only have a short time at home. Breastfeeding is definitely worth it – for your baby, you, and your entire family. With loving support, you can enjoy all of the benefits it provides.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,28,28,'und',0,'<p>Get off to a good start when your baby arrives - learn about breastfeeding now and find tips for before your baby arrives, when baby is here, and when you are way from baby.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,31,31,'und',0,'<p>Highlights WIC’s commitment and success in breastfeeding promotion and support, and invites stakeholders and health care professionals to partner with WIC to create a national environment that encourages mothers to breastfeed. Watch the <a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/32\">video</a>&nbsp;and download the video booklet.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,32,32,'und',0,'<p><iframe class=\"vzaar-video-player\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"326\" id=\"vzvd-1038281\" name=\"vzvd-1038281\" src=\"http://view.vzaar.com/1038281/player\" title=\"vzaar video player\" width=\"576\"></iframe></p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','ls_content',0,33,33,'und',0,'<p>Resources available as part of a continual effort to increase breastfeeding initiation and duration rates among African American women by involving fathers in breastfeeding promotion efforts. Limited printed copies and an accompanying DVD are available to <a href=\"http://www.fns.usda.gov/wic/fathers-supporting-breastfeeding\">order</a>.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,34,34,'und',0,'<p>When your children become parents themselves, they turn to you for advice. They value your experience when they make their decisions about how to take care of your grandchildren; especially when it comes to feeding their newborn babies.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,35,35,'und',0,'<p>As you and your partner expand your family, you will have many new experiences. Taking care of your family is a big responsibility, and you want to protect them and make healthy choices. Encouraging your partner to breastfeed is important.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,36,36,'und',0,'<p>Support the breastfeeding mom in your life with these tips to promote her comfort and relaxation. Remember to&nbsp; make time for you and baby. Babies need cuddles and skin-to-skin time with their dads, too. You can also bathe, diaper and play with baby.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,38,38,'und',0,'<p>Use these materials to promote Loving Support Makes Breastfeeding Work© in your agency or office. If you need assistance with using or printing the materials, contact the <a href=\"http://mailto:wicworks@ars.usda.gov\">WIC Works Team</a>.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,39,39,'und',0,'<p>Culturally appropriate tools to effectively communicate with Hispanic participants about the benefits of breastfeeding. <a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/40\">View</a> the accompanying video or <a href=\"http://www.fns.usda.gov/sites/default/files/MagicalBondOrderForm.pdf\">order</a> the video and materials.</p>\r\n','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;\r\n<p>&nbsp;\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>\r\n</p>\r\n','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,40,40,'und',0,'<p>This three-time-award-winning video-novella follows a discussion about breastfeeding among WIC mothers and family members. Animated characters, Princessa Tigressa, her baby Pepito, and Mother Hen, add an element of “magic” to the presentation as they address common misconceptions about breastfeeding.</p>\r\n<iframe allowFullScreen allowTransparency=\"true\" class=\"vzaar video player\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"562\" id=\"vzpl-1135\" mozallowfullscreen name=\"vzpl-1135\" src=\"http://view.vzaar.com/playlists/1135\" title=\"vzaar video player\" type=\"text/html\" webkitAllowFullScreen width=\"576\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n','','full_html'),('node','ls_content',0,41,41,'und',0,'<p>Resources available as part of a continual effort to increase breastfeeding initiation and duration rates among African American women by involving fathers in breastfeeding promotion efforts. <a href=\"http://www.fns.usda.gov/wic/fathers-supporting-breastfeeding\">Order</a> the materials.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','ls_content',0,42,42,'und',0,'<p>This standardized competency-based curriculum was developed to ensure that all staff attain a level of proficiency in the skills required to promote and support breastfeeding in the WIC setting. View the accompanying <a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/43\">videos</a>. If you need assistance with using or printing the materials, contact the <a href=\"http://mailto:wicworks@ars.usda.gov\">WIC Works Team</a>.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,43,43,'und',0,'<iframe allowFullScreen allowTransparency=\"true\" class=\"vzaar video player\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"466\" id=\"vzpl-937\" name=\"vzpl-937\" src=\"http://view.vzaar.com/playlists/937\" title=\"vzaar video player\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"448\"></iframe>','','full_html'),('node','ls_content',0,47,47,'und',0,'<p>In 2011, the FNS peer counseling training curricula were updated: <strong>Loving Support© Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together – For WIC Managers</strong> and<strong> Loving Support© Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together – For Training WIC Peer Counselors</strong>.&nbsp; These curricula were developed as a result of a cooperative agreement with Every Mother, Inc., a nonprofit organization providing counseling and lactation training and technical assistance to healthcare professionals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/51\">Download the complete training packages</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/52\">View instructional tools and support materials</a>.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,50,50,'und',0,'<p><strong>Peer Counseling: Making a Difference for WIC Families </strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe use of breastfeeding peer counselors adds a critical dimension to WIC’s efforts to help women initiate and continue breastfeeding.&nbsp; WIC breastfeeding peer counselors provide a valuable service to their communities, addressing the barriers to breastfeeding by offering breastfeeding education, support, and role modeling.&nbsp;&nbsp; Peer counselors are familiar with the resources available to WIC clients, have familiarity with the questions a new breastfeeding mother may ask, and recognize when to refer mothers to other resources during critical periods when mothers may experience difficulty.&nbsp; The goal of the Food and Nutrition Service (FNS) is to integrate peer counseling as a WIC service in every WIC clinic.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn 2004 FNS developed a training and technical assistance project to equip WIC Programs with a framework for designing and maintaining peer counseling programs.&nbsp;&nbsp; “Using <em>Loving Support</em>© to Implement Best Practices in Peer Counseling” included formative research to understand barriers and motivators to implementing and sustaining peer counseling programs and development of training curricula for managers and peer counselors.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key Elements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Formative research to understand barriers and motivators to implementing and sustaining peer counseling&nbsp;programs and to identify training needs. <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/research_brief.pdf\" target=\"new\">2004 Formative Research Brief.</a></li>\r\n	<li>Implementing and sustaining peer counseling programs and to identify training needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Identification of best practices</li>\r\n	<li>Development of <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/FNS_model.pdf\" target=\"new\">Loving Support© Model</a>&nbsp; for successful peer counseling programs.</li>\r\n	<li>Development of two <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/support_peer_materials.html\">training curricula</a> for WIC staff.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Report</strong><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/peer_counseling_study.pdf\" target=\"new\">WIC Breastfeeding Peer Counseling Study Final Implementation Report June 2010</a><br />\r\n<u><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/bfshowcase.pdf\" target=\"new\">Peer Counseling Success Stories: Implementing and Expanding Breastfeeding Peer Counseling Programs</a></u> - NWA Nutrition and Breastfeeding 2006 Conference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who are Breastfeeding Peer Counselors and What Do They Do?</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nPeer counselors are mothers who have personal experience with breastfeeding and are trained to provide basic breastfeeding information and support to other mothers with whom they share various characteristics, such as language, race/ethnicity, and socioeconomic status. &nbsp;Peer counselors reinforce breastfeeding recommendations in a socially and culturally appropriate context, and promote breastfeeding as an important element in the healthy development of the mother and baby.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn WIC, peer counselors are recruited and hired from WIC’s target population of low-income women and undergo training to provide mother-to-mother support in group settings and one-to-one counseling through telephone calls or visits in the home, clinic, or hospital.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Loving Support© Model&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nThe <a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/FNS_model.pdf\">Loving Support© Model</a> for a Succesful Peer Counseling Program is the framework for WIC Programs to establish policies and practices under each of its required components. The Loving Support© Model addresses program support in two areas:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n- Adequate program support from State and local management.<br />\r\n- Adequate program support of peer counselors.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,51,51,'und',0,'<p>The WIC Peer Counselor Training Curriculum is a single, very large zipped folder (approx. 3 GB) containing PowerPoint slide shows, video clips, and other files. While developed for WIC, anyone can use it for training breastfeeding peer counselors or other breastfeeding support personnel. The downloads may take a long time (up to one hour) and are delivered via Dropbox. Contact the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"mailto:wicworks@ars.usda.gov\">WIC Works Team</a> to request a copy of the training on a flash drive. Download the training via the links below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/8hf2yiis84ccybn/WIC_PC_Curriculum.zip?m\">PC Version - English</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/kthl04e0unx5j1k/WIC_Training_SP.zip\">PC Version - Spanish</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/tsb1e0ogzginvh4/WIC_Training_MAC.zip\">MAC Version</a></p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,52,52,'und',0,'<p>This set of videos and tools can help you more effectively use the training platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/53\">Overview Webinars</a> (overview of how to use the training, as well as explains the concepts in the manager\'s training)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/54\">Instructional Videos</a> (how to download and use the training platform)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/55\">Sample Videos from Training Platform</a></li>\r\n	<li>Manager Training\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/ManagementTrainingSpeakerNotes.pdf\">Speaker Notes</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/ManagerPrompts.pdf\">Facilitator Prompts</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/ManagementTrainingHandouts.pdf\">Handouts</a></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Peer Counselor Training\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PCTrainingSpeakerNotes.pdf\">Speaker Notes</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PCPrompts.pdf\">Facilitator Prompts</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PCTrainingHandoutsBW.pdf\">Handouts</a> (B&amp;W)</li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PCTrainingHandoutsColor.pdf\">Handouts</a> (Color)</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Peer Counselor Handbook\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/Handbook/BinderCovers.pdf\">Covers</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/Handbook/BinderSpine.pdf\">Spine</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/Handbook/BinderTabs.pdf\">Tabs</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/Handbook/TrainingModules.pdf\">Training Modules</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/Handbook/HandoutsBW.pdf\">Handouts</a> (B&amp;W)</li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/Handbook/HandoutsColor.pdf\">Handouts</a> (Color)</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/59\">Podcasts for Peer Counselors</a></li>\r\n	<li>Sample Certificates\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/SampleCertificate1.pdf\">Version 1</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/SampleCertificate2.pdf\">Version 2</a></li>\r\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/SampleCertificate3.pdf\">Version 3</a></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/56\">Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/57\">Tips for Personalizing Your Training Platform</a></li>\r\n	<li><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/TrainingIdeas.pdf\" target=\"new\">Creative Training Ideas and Recommendations from State WIC Agencies</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://loving.bluepresley.com/node/58\">Photo Credits/Permissions for Images Used in the Peer Counseling Training Platform</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,53,53,'und',0,'<p><iframe class=\"vzaar video player\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"466\" id=\"vzpl-966\" name=\"vzpl-966\" src=\"http://view.vzaar.com/playlists/966\" title=\"vzaar video player\" width=\"448\"></iframe><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a id=\"list\" name=\"list\"></a><strong>Webinar #1: Using the WIC Peer Counselor Platform</strong> [01:05:10]<br />\r\nFor trainers interested in learning how to use the peer counseling training platform to train peer counselors.&nbsp; Includes an overview of the platform, including the computer equipment necessary to run it and how to use the curriculum components.&nbsp;Watch the webinar above or <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar1_UsingPlatform.wmv\"><strong>download</strong></a> [WMV] it to your computer. Download the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar1Script.pdf\" target=\"new\"><strong>script</strong></a> [PDF] for the webinar.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Webinar #1A - More Tips on Using the Platform</strong> [00:33:26]<br />\r\nThis webcast includes step-by-step instructions for linking State-specific materials to the platform.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>NOTE:&nbsp; </strong>Webinars #1 and #2 demonstrate how to download the peer counseling training materials from the website of Aspire Communications.&nbsp;&nbsp; However the latest materials can now be downloaded from the WIC Works Resource System--you do not need to go to Aspire Communications website.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe instructions for downloading, unzipping and navigating remain the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Webinar #2: WIC Managers - Peer Counseling Program Planning</strong> [00:46:28]<br />\r\nSuccessful peer counseling programs do not just “happen.”&nbsp; They occur when State and local agencies plan for success by assembling a supportive team and developing a program that addresses the needs of WIC mothers and the support of peer counselors.&nbsp;&nbsp; This webcast provides a summary of key highlights on program planning from Sections 1, 3 and 4 of <em>Loving Support Through Peer Counseling:&nbsp; A Journey Together (for Managers).&nbsp; </em>Watch the webinar above or <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/webinar2.wmv\"><strong>download</strong></a> [WMV] it to your computer. Download the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar2Script.pdf\" target=\"new\"><strong>script</strong></a> [PDF] for the webinar.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Webinar #3: WIC Managers: &nbsp;Peer Counselor Staffing Considerations </strong>[00:27:12]<br />\r\nHiring the right people as peer counselors helps a program get off to the best start.&nbsp; This webcast addresses important qualities to seek when hiring peer counselors and considerations in hiring and employing peer counselors.&nbsp; The webcast provides a summary of key highlights from Section 5 of <em>Loving Support Through Peer Counseling:&nbsp; A Journey Together (for Managers).&nbsp; </em> Watch the webinar above or <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/webinar3staffing.wmv\"><strong>download</strong></a> [WMV] it to your computer. Download the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar3Script.pdf\" target=\"new\"><strong>script</strong></a> [PDF] for the webinar.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Webinar #4: Scope of Practice for Peer Counselors</strong> [00:24:53]<br />\r\nThe peer counselor scope of practice is limited to supporting normal breastfeeding. &nbsp;This means providing basic information and support, including: Performing in a professional manner in all aspects of her role; encouraging and supporting mothers to breastfeed; teaching basic breastfeeding to WIC mothers, supporting mothers when difficulties occur, and yielding to breastfeeding experts.&nbsp; Peer counselors do not provide services beyond their basic scope of practice.&nbsp; This webcast provides a summary of key highlights of Section 6 of <em>Loving Support Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together (for Managers).</em> Watch the webinar above or <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar4.wmv\"><strong>download</strong></a> [WMV] it to your computer. Download the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar4Script.pdf\" target=\"new\"><strong>script</strong></a> [PDF] for the webinar.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Webinar #5 Practice Settings for Peer Counselors</strong> [00:29:44]<br />\r\nResearch shows that the key to success with peer counseling is being available to mothers when they need it most.&nbsp; Peer counselors help fill the gap in breastfeeding services. &nbsp;They can do this by working in a variety of locations to serve the needs of WIC mothers such as making telephone calls from home, and making hospital and home visits.&nbsp; This webcast provides a summary of key highlights of Section 7 of <em>Loving Support Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together (for Managers).</em> Watch the webinar above or <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar5.wmv\"><strong>download</strong></a> [WMV] it to your computer. Download the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar5Script.pdf\" target=\"new\"><strong>script</strong></a> [PDF] for the webinar.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Webinar #6 Mentoring and Supervising Peer Counselors</strong> [00:32:08]<br />\r\nAdequate and appropriate supervision, monitoring and support of peer counselors is integral to sustaining a successful peer counseling program.&nbsp; This webcast provides a summary of key highlights of Sections 9 and 10 of <em>Loving Support Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together (for Managers).</em> Watch the webinar above or <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar5.wmv\"><strong>download</strong></a> [WMV] it to your computer. Download the <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/webinars/Webinar6Script.pdf\" target=\"new\"><strong>script</strong></a> [PDF] for the webinar.</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','page',0,54,54,'und',0,'<iframe allowFullScreen allowTransparency=\"true\" class=\"vzaar video player\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"566\" id=\"vzpl-1129\" name=\"vzpl-1129\" src=\"http://view.vzaar.com/playlists/1129\" title=\"vzaar video player\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"576\"></iframe>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','page',0,55,55,'und',0,'<p>Watch a selection of videos from the training below (English and Spanish). View <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/videosummaries.pdf\" target=\"new\">summaries</a> [PDF] of all videos from the training (courtesy of the Western Region WIC States).<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<iframe class=\"vzaar video player\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"336\" id=\"vzpl-1095\" name=\"vzpl-1095\" src=\"http://view.vzaar.com/playlists/1095\" title=\"vzaar video player\" width=\"607\"></iframe></p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','page',0,56,56,'und',0,'<p><strong>How did this innovative peer counseling training program come about?</strong><br />\r\nThe USDA Food and Nutrition Service entered into a cooperative agreement with <em>Every Mother, Inc. </em>to develop the curriculum package, “<em>Loving Support</em>© Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together,” which includes two curricula: “<em>Loving Support</em>© Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together – For WIC Managers” and “<em>Loving Support</em>© Through Peer Counseling: A Journey Together – For Training WIC Peer Counselors.” Feedback from an expert panel and best practice interviews with WIC State and local agency staff in each USDA geographic region were valuable in building the content, and WIC agencies across the U.S. contributed hundreds of photos, videos, and stories to help create memorable, meaningful visuals. The flexible presentation concepts were developed by Robert Lane with <em>Aspire Communications</em>. The curriculum design was developed by <em>Rich Winter Design &amp; Multimedia</em>. The YouTube© videos were created by <em>Vision Way Media, Inc.</em> in Denver.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the research basis behind this kind of visually interactive training?</strong><br />\r\nRefer to your <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/TrainingFacilitatorGuide.pdf\">Training Facilitator Guide</a><em> </em>for a thorough summary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What if the platform doesn’t work properly on my computer?</strong><br />\r\nIf for some reason your platform doesn’t seem to work properly as explained above - for example the hyperlinks don’t work or the videos don’t play - double check the following items.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Is PowerPoint 2008 or higher installed on your computer?&nbsp; Remember that the platform will not work properly with PowerPoint Viewer or an Open Office version of presentation software.</li>\r\n	<li>Did you actually unzip or extract the platform folder after downloading?&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Are you in slide show mode? &nbsp;The hyperlinks do not work until you start the slide show.</li>\r\n	<li>Are you using the correct platform type for PC or Mac computer?&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Does your IT department have special security or firewalls in place that might prevent the slide show from working properly?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>When playing video clips, note that some of the clips have a few seconds of static title at the beginning and the video may not seem to be playing. Just let it play for a few seconds until the actual content begins. During this time, do not click the screen or the video will pause. If you do accidentally pause the video with a click, simply click the screen again to restart the video.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If these steps don’t solve the problem, try using a newer computer if yours is old. If all else fails, feel free to contact us via the support button at the top of the page for additional trouble shooting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Can we include some of our own pictures and videos?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>While you may wish to make changes to the training platform and personalize it to your State or local needs, FNS strongly encourages you NOT to directly alter the downloaded platform. Here’s why:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The presentation platform is a very sophisticated collection of hyperlinked slide shows. Changing photos or making other revisions to the slides or platform can easily mess up the navigation system if you are unfamiliar with the skills used to create it.</li>\r\n	<li>Any modifications made to the training platform now will be overwritten and lost when you download an updated and expanded version in the future.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>A recommended alternative is to create a simple presentation separate from the main platform and then link to it.&nbsp;That way you’ll be able to jump back and forth between the standard WIC peer counselor platform and your own state or local content as needed.&nbsp;It’s easy to do.&nbsp;Here’s how:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Create a folder called <em>StateLocal </em>and place it on your desktop.&nbsp;Name your State or local specific slide show<em>, StateLocal.pptx</em>. For the links to work, you cannot rename these and your presentation must remain within the “StateLocal” folder on your desktop.&nbsp;To access the presentation from the main peer counselor platform, simply click the “State/Local” button on the dashboard.&nbsp;When you scroll past the last slide it will automatically return to the dashboard on the main peer counselor platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need more sophisticated methods of navigation or wish to develop your presentation into a more comprehensive, interactive presentation platform, visit the support page to contact an Aspire representative.&nbsp;He or she will help you explore appropriate options such as onsite or Web-based training workshops, books, consultation, or contract work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Does this platform work on an iPad or other tablets?</strong><br />\r\nCurrently, no, unless your tablet happens to run Windows 7 and you have PowerPoint installed on it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Does this platform work on a Mac computer?</strong><br />\r\nYes, a Mac version of the platform is available for download. However, we still recommend using the PC version on a PC computer if possible because PowerPoint running on a Mac is less efficient, resulting in longer delays when opening content.&nbsp;Be sure to download the Mac version if preferred and follow all related instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Where do I get the air mouse you recommend for this kind of presentation?</strong><br />\r\nIt can be ordered from several places, try search sites such as Amazon.com.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How often do you update the platform with new material?</strong><br />\r\nUpdates will occur approximately every 3 months through 2012. FNS regional offices will be notified when updates are available and will share this information with WIC State agencies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Can we use photos and videos from the platform in our other WIC materials and training resources? </strong>See <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/support_peer_images.html\">Photo Credits/Permissions for Images Used in the Peer Counseling Training Platform</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Should this platform be used with WIC participants?</strong><br />\r\nWhile certain components of the platform may be useful in WIC participant education settings, the curriculum was designed for training WIC peer counselors and their managers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Will the platform and materials be available in Spanish? </strong><br />\r\nYes. The peer counseling slides in the platform will be translated into Spanish. Also, the handouts and narrative summaries of each module in the <em>Peer Counselor Handbook</em> will be translated by early spring, 2012.&nbsp;The videos created for the project will also include Spanish subtitles.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,57,57,'und',0,'<p><strong>Personalizing the Platform</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile you may wish to make changes to the training platform and personalize it to your State or local needs, FNS strongly encourages you NOT to directly alter the downloaded platform. Here’s why:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The presentation platform is a very sophisticated collection of hyperlinked slide shows. Changing photos or making other revisions to the slides or platform can easily mess up the navigation system if you are unfamiliar with the skills used to create it.</li>\r\n	<li>Any modifications made to the training platform now will be overwritten and lost when you download an updated and expanded version in the future.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nA recommended alternative is to create a simple presentation separate from the main platform and then link to it.&nbsp;That way you’ll be able to jump back and forth between the standard WIC peer counselor platform and your own state or local content as needed.&nbsp;It’s easy to do.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHere’s how:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Create a folder called <em>StateLocal </em>and place it on your desktop.&nbsp;Name your State or local specific slide show<em>, StateLocal.pptx</em>. For the links to work, you cannot rename these and your presentation must remain within the “StateLocal” folder on your desktop.&nbsp;To access the presentation from the main peer counselor platform, simply click the “State/Local” button on the dashboard.&nbsp;When you scroll past the last slide it will automatically return to the dashboard on the main peer counselor platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Watch <a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/support_peer_webinars.html\">webinar #1A</a> for step-by-step instructions for linking State-specific information to the platform.</p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,58,58,'und',0,'<p><strong>Photo Credits/Permissions for Images Used in the Peer Counseling Training Platform</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are interested in using any of the images from the Peer Counseling Training Platform, please view the documents below to find out about the photo credits/permissions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To extract images from the platform, follow these steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. In My Computer, browse to and open the WIC PC Curriculum Folder<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. Open the WIC PC Platform Folder<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3. Open the folder for the module you want to look it, then open the PowerPoint file that is &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;associated with the image<br />\r\n<br />\r\n4. Locate the image in the slides, right click on the image and save it to your computer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Photo Credits/Permission Information:</strong> [PDF]<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module1.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 1</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module2.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 2</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module3.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 3</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module4.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 4</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module5.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 5</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module6.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 6</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module7.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 7</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module8.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 8</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module9.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 9</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module10.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 10</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module11.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 11</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module12.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 12</a><br />\r\n<a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/PhotoCredits_Module13.pdf\" target=\"new\">Module 13</a></p>\r\n','','filtered_html'),('node','page',0,59,59,'und',0,'<p>Podcasts have been created to supplement the peer counselor training experience, and can be used<br />\r\nto reinforce key messages in the curriculum as part of the initial training, monthly peer counselor staff meetings, or for peer counselors to download to mobile devices. The podcasts are available as part of the presentation platform but are available for easy access here.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:574px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Talking with Moms: Using Open-Ended Questions<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts/one_final.wmv\">WMV</a></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts/one_final.mp4\">MP4</a></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts/one_final.mp3\">MP3</a></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Talking with Moms: Affirmation<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts/two_final.wmv\">WMV</a></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts/two_final.mp4\">MP4</a></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts/two_final.mp3\">MP3</a></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Talking with Moms in Tough Situations<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<th scope=\"col\"><a class=\"styleone\" href=\"http://www.nal.usda.gov/wicworks/Learning_Center/PC/podcasts