INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (5,'node',' help faqs faqs placeholder  ',0),(6,'node',' contact us contact us subject message  ',0),(13,'node',' about loving support loving support makes breastfeeding work is the united states department of agriculture s usda national breastfeeding promotion and support campaign education training and outreach materials are provided for staff of the special supplemental nutrition program for women infants and children wic resources are also available for women and their families friends and health care providers community partners key messages helping women feel comfortable with breastfeeding tips on how breastfeeding can work around a busy schedule the involvement of family and friends to make breastfeeding a success campaign goals increase breastfeeding initiation rates among wic participants increase breastfeeding duration among wic participants increase referrals to wic for breastfeeding support increase general public acceptance and support of breastfeeding provide support and technical assistance to wic state and local agencies in the promotion of breastfeeding key messages  ',0),(24,'node',' you have everything your baby needs learning how to breastfeed takes time and patience here are some frequent questions new mothers have about breastfeeding you have everything your baby needs english version you have everything your baby needs spanish version moms ',0),(25,'node',' encouragement most people think of breastfeeding as something just between mom and baby the truth is breastfeeding is a special time for everyone breastfeeding gives mom dad grandparents and the entire family a reason to be proud and become part of the new baby s life encouragement moms ',0),(26,'node',' confidence many new mothers worry about breastfeeding around others even around people they know with a little planning and practice they soon find they can breastfeed anytime anywhere and you will too confidence moms ',0),(27,'node',' busy moms juggling work school family friends or other demands might make you nervous about breastfeeding or wonder if it s worth it if you only have a short time at home breastfeeding is definitely worth it for your baby you and your entire family with loving support you can enjoy all of the benefits it provides busy moms moms ',0),(28,'node',' ready set breastfeed  get off to a good start when your baby arrives learn about breastfeeding now and find tips for before your baby arrives when baby is here and when you are way from baby ready set breastfeed  moms ',0),(31,'node',' partnering with wic for breastfeeding success highlights wic s commitment and success in breastfeeding promotion and support and invites stakeholders and health care professionals to partner with wic to create a national environment that encourages mothers to breastfeed watch the video  and download the video booklet partnering with wic for breastfeeding success video booklet community partners ',0),(32,'node',' partnering with wic for breastfeeding success video  video  ',0),(33,'node',' fathers supporting breastfeeding resources available as part of a continual effort to increase breastfeeding initiation and duration rates among african american women by involving fathers in breastfeeding promotion efforts limited printed copies and an accompanying dvd are available to order  fathers can support breastfeeding poster farthers can support breastfeeding brochure making the decision poster making the decision brochure family friends ',0),(34,'node',' grandparents play an important role when your children become parents themselves they turn to you for advice they value your experience when they make their decisions about how to take care of your grandchildren especially when it comes to feeding their newborn babies grandparents play an important role english version grandparents play an important role spanish version family friends ',0),(35,'node',' dads play an important role as you and your partner expand your family you will have many new experiences taking care of your family is a big responsibility and you want to protect them and make healthy choices encouraging your partner to breastfeed is important dads play an important role english version dads play an important role spanish version family friends ',0),(36,'node',' 10 tips for dads support the breastfeeding mom in your life with these tips to promote her comfort and relaxation remember to make time for you and baby babies need cuddles and skintoskin time with their dads too you can also bathe diaper and play with baby 10 tips for dads family friends ',0),(38,'node',' campaign materials use these materials to promote loving support makes breastfeeding work in your agency or office if you need assistance with using or printing the materials contact the wic works team  campaign materials wic staff message graphic small message graphic large sizes busy moms poster busy moms handout confidence poster confidence handout encouragement poster encouragement handout ready set breastfeed  10 tips for dads ',0),(39,'node',' magical bond of love culturally appropriate tools to effectively communicate with hispanic participants about the benefits of breastfeeding view the accompanying video or order the video and materials magical bond of love wic staff project summary video discussion guide you have everything your baby needs english version you have everything your baby needs spanish version dads play an important role english version dads play an important role spanish version grandparents play an important role english version grandparents play an important role spanish version ',0),(40,'node',' magical bond of love video this threetimeawardwinning videonovella follows a discussion about breastfeeding among wic mothers and family members animated characters princessa tigressa her baby pepito and mother hen add an element of magic to the presentation as they address common misconceptions about breastfeeding  view  ',0),(41,'node',' fathers supporting breastfeeding resources available as part of a continual effort to increase breastfeeding initiation and duration rates among african american women by involving fathers in breastfeeding promotion efforts order the materials fathers supporting breastfeeding wic staff fathers can support breastfeeding brochure fathers can support breastfeeding poster making the decision brochure making the decision poster ',0),(42,'node',' grow and glow in wic this standardized competencybased curriculum was developed to ensure that all staff attain a level of proficiency in the skills required to promote and support breastfeeding in the wic setting view the accompanying videos  if you need assistance with using or printing the materials contact the wic works team  grow and glow in wic wic staff module 1 wic supports breastfeeding ppt  module 2 feelings about breastfeeding ppt  module 3 communicating presentation ppt  module 4 barriers ppt  module 5 exclusive breastfeeding ppt  module 6 pregnancy ppt  module 7 new moms ppt  module 8 continuing breastfeeding ppt  module 9 separation ppt  module 10 solutions for problems ppt  speaker notes worksheets posters activity flower wic gardener s journal goal flower covers and dividers ',0),(43,'node',' grow and glow videos  videos  ',0),(47,'node',' peer counseling in 2011 the fns peer counseling training curricula were updated  loving support through peer counseling a journey together for wic managers and loving support through peer counseling a journey together for training wic peer counselors  these curricula were developed as a result of a cooperative agreement with every mother inc a nonprofit organization providing counseling and lactation training and technical assistance to healthcare professionals  download the complete training packages  view instructional tools and support materials  peer counseling wic staff ',0),(50,'node',' about wic breastfeeding peer counseling peer counseling making a difference for wic families the use of breastfeeding peer counselors adds a critical dimension to wic s efforts to help women initiate and continue breastfeeding wic breastfeeding peer counselors provide a valuable service to their communities addressing the barriers to breastfeeding by offering breastfeeding education support and role modeling peer counselors are familiar with the resources available to wic clients have familiarity with the questions a new breastfeeding mother may ask and recognize when to refer mothers to other resources during critical periods when mothers may experience difficulty the goal of the food and nutrition service fns is to integrate peer counseling as a wic service in every wic clinic in 2004 fns developed a training and technical assistance project to equip wic programs with a framework for designing and maintaining peer counseling programs using loving support  to implement best practices in peer counseling included formative research to understand barriers and motivators to implementing and sustaining peer counseling programs and development of training curricula for managers and peer counselors  key elements  formative research to understand barriers and motivators to implementing and sustaining peer counseling programs and to identify training needs 2004 formative research brief implementing and sustaining peer counseling programs and to identify training needs identification of best practices development of loving support model  for successful peer counseling programs development of two training curricula for wic staff report wic breastfeeding peer counseling study final implementation report june 2010 peer counseling success stories implementing and expanding breastfeeding peer counseling programs  nwa nutrition and breastfeeding 2006 conference who are breastfeeding peer counselors and what do they do  peer counselors are mothers who have personal experience with breastfeeding and are trained to provide basic breastfeeding information and support to other mothers with whom they share various characteristics such as language race ethnicity and socioeconomic status peer counselors reinforce breastfeeding recommendations in a socially and culturally appropriate context and promote breastfeeding as an important element in the healthy development of the mother and baby in wic peer counselors are recruited and hired from wic s target population of lowincome women and undergo training to provide mothertomother support in group settings and onetoone counseling through telephone calls or visits in the home clinic or hospital  loving support model  the loving support model for a succesful peer counseling program is the framework for wic programs to establish policies and practices under each of its required components the loving support model addresses program support in two areas adequate program support from state and local management adequate program support of peer counselors  ',0),(51,'node',' downloads the wic peer counselor training curriculum is a single very large zipped folder approx 3 gb containing powerpoint slide shows video clips and other files while developed for wic anyone can use it for training breastfeeding peer counselors or other breastfeeding support personnel the downloads may take a long time up to one hour and are delivered via dropbox contact the wic works team to request a copy of the training on a flash drive download the training via the links below pc version english pc version spanish mac version  download the complete training packages  ',0),(52,'node',' instructional tools and support materials this set of videos and tools can help you more effectively use the training platform overview webinars  overview of how to use the training as well as explains the concepts in the manager s training  instructional videos  how to download and use the training platform  sample videos from training platform manager training speaker notes facilitator prompts handouts peer counselor training speaker notes facilitator prompts handouts  b w  handouts  color peer counselor handbook covers spine tabs training modules handouts  b w  handouts  color  podcasts for peer counselors sample certificates version 1 version 2 version 3 frequently asked questions tips for personalizing your training platform creative training ideas and recommendations from state wic agencies photo credits permissions for images used in the peer counseling training platform    view instructional tools and support materials  ',0),(53,'node',' overview webinars webinar 1 using the wic peer counselor platform  10510 for trainers interested in learning how to use the peer counseling training platform to train peer counselors includes an overview of the platform including the computer equipment necessary to run it and how to use the curriculum components watch the webinar above or download  wmv it to your computer download the script  pdf for the webinar webinar 1a more tips on using the platform  3326 this webcast includes stepbystep instructions for linking statespecific materials to the platform  note  webinars 1 and 2 demonstrate how to download the peer counseling training materials from the website of aspire communications however the latest materials can now be downloaded from the wic works resource system you do not need to go to aspire communications website the instructions for downloading unzipping and navigating remain the same webinar 2 wic managers peer counseling program planning  4628 successful peer counseling programs do not just happen they occur when state and local agencies plan for success by assembling a supportive team and developing a program that addresses the needs of wic mothers and the support of peer counselors this webcast provides a summary of key highlights on program planning from sections 1 3 and 4 of loving support through peer counseling a journey together for managers  watch the webinar above or download  wmv it to your computer download the script  pdf for the webinar webinar 3 wic managers peer counselor staffing considerations  2712 hiring the right people as peer counselors helps a program get off to the best start this webcast addresses important qualities to seek when hiring peer counselors and considerations in hiring and employing peer counselors the webcast provides a summary of key highlights from section 5 of loving support through peer counseling a journey together for managers  watch the webinar above or download  wmv it to your computer download the script  pdf for the webinar webinar 4 scope of practice for peer counselors  2453 the peer counselor scope of practice is limited to supporting normal breastfeeding this means providing basic information and support including performing in a professional manner in all aspects of her role encouraging and supporting mothers to breastfeed teaching basic breastfeeding to wic mothers supporting mothers when difficulties occur and yielding to breastfeeding experts peer counselors do not provide services beyond their basic scope of practice this webcast provides a summary of key highlights of section 6 of loving support through peer counseling a journey together for managers  watch the webinar above or download  wmv it to your computer download the script  pdf for the webinar webinar 5 practice settings for peer counselors  2944 research shows that the key to success with peer counseling is being available to mothers when they need it most peer counselors help fill the gap in breastfeeding services they can do this by working in a variety of locations to serve the needs of wic mothers such as making telephone calls from home and making hospital and home visits this webcast provides a summary of key highlights of section 7 of loving support through peer counseling a journey together for managers  watch the webinar above or download  wmv it to your computer download the script  pdf for the webinar webinar 6 mentoring and supervising peer counselors  3208 adequate and appropriate supervision monitoring and support of peer counselors is integral to sustaining a successful peer counseling program this webcast provides a summary of key highlights of sections 9 and 10 of loving support through peer counseling a journey together for managers  watch the webinar above or download  wmv it to your computer download the script  pdf for the webinar  overview webinars  ',0),(54,'node',' instructional videos  instructional videos  ',0),(55,'node',' sample videos from training platform watch a selection of videos from the training below english and spanish view summaries  pdf of all videos from the training courtesy of the western region wic states   sample videos from training platform  ',0),(56,'node',' frequently asked questions how did this innovative peer counseling training program come about  the usda food and nutrition service entered into a cooperative agreement with every mother inc to develop the curriculum package  loving support  through peer counseling a journey together which includes two curricula  loving support  through peer counseling a journey together for wic managers and  loving support  through peer counseling a journey together for training wic peer counselors feedback from an expert panel and best practice interviews with wic state and local agency staff in each usda geographic region were valuable in building the content and wic agencies across the us contributed hundreds of photos videos and stories to help create memorable meaningful visuals the flexible presentation concepts were developed by robert lane with aspire communications  the curriculum design was developed by rich winter design multimedia  the youtube videos were created by vision way media inc in denver what is the research basis behind this kind of visually interactive training  refer to your training facilitator guide for a thorough summary what if the platform doesn t work properly on my computer  if for some reason your platform doesn t seem to work properly as explained above for example the hyperlinks don t work or the videos don t play double check the following items is powerpoint 2008 or higher installed on your computer remember that the platform will not work properly with powerpoint viewer or an open office version of presentation software did you actually unzip or extract the platform folder after downloading are you in slide show mode the hyperlinks do not work until you start the slide show are you using the correct platform type for pc or mac computer does your it department have special security or firewalls in place that might prevent the slide show from working properly when playing video clips note that some of the clips have a few seconds of static title at the beginning and the video may not seem to be playing just let it play for a few seconds until the actual content begins during this time do not click the screen or the video will pause if you do accidentally pause the video with a click simply click the screen again to restart the video if these steps don t solve the problem try using a newer computer if yours is old if all else fails feel free to contact us via the support button at the top of the page for additional trouble shooting can we include some of our own pictures and videos  while you may wish to make changes to the training platform and personalize it to your state or local needs fns strongly encourages you not to directly alter the downloaded platform here s why the presentation platform is a very sophisticated collection of hyperlinked slide shows changing photos or making other revisions to the slides or platform can easily mess up the navigation system if you are unfamiliar with the skills used to create it any modifications made to the training platform now will be overwritten and lost when you download an updated and expanded version in the future a recommended alternative is to create a simple presentation separate from the main platform and then link to it that way you ll be able to jump back and forth between the standard wic peer counselor platform and your own state or local content as needed it s easy to do here s how create a folder called statelocal and place it on your desktop name your state or local specific slide show  statelocalpptx  for the links to work you cannot rename these and your presentation must remain within the statelocal folder on your desktop to access the presentation from the main peer counselor platform simply click the state local button on the dashboard when you scroll past the last slide it will automatically return to the dashboard on the main peer counselor platform if you need more sophisticated methods of navigation or wish to develop your presentation into a more comprehensive interactive presentation platform visit the support page to contact an aspire representative he or she will help you explore appropriate options such as onsite or webbased training workshops books consultation or contract work does this platform work on an ipad or other tablets  currently no unless your tablet happens to run windows 7 and you have powerpoint installed on it does this platform work on a mac computer  yes a mac version of the platform is available for download however we still recommend using the pc version on a pc computer if possible because powerpoint running on a mac is less efficient resulting in longer delays when opening content be sure to download the mac version if preferred and follow all related instructions where do i get the air mouse you recommend for this kind of presentation  it can be ordered from several places try search sites such as amazoncom  how often do you update the platform with new material  updates will occur approximately every 3 months through 2012 fns regional offices will be notified when updates are available and will share this information with wic state agencies can we use photos and videos from the platform in our other wic materials and training resources  see photo credits permissions for images used in the peer counseling training platform  should this platform be used with wic participants  while certain components of the platform may be useful in wic participant education settings the curriculum was designed for training wic peer counselors and their managers  will the platform and materials be available in spanish  yes the peer counseling slides in the platform will be translated into spanish also the handouts and narrative summaries of each module in the peer counselor handbook will be translated by early spring 2012 the videos created for the project will also include spanish subtitles  frequently asked questions  ',0),(57,'node',' tips for personalizing your training platform personalizing the platform while you may wish to make changes to the training platform and personalize it to your state or local needs fns strongly encourages you not to directly alter the downloaded platform here s why the presentation platform is a very sophisticated collection of hyperlinked slide shows changing photos or making other revisions to the slides or platform can easily mess up the navigation system if you are unfamiliar with the skills used to create it any modifications made to the training platform now will be overwritten and lost when you download an updated and expanded version in the future a recommended alternative is to create a simple presentation separate from the main platform and then link to it that way you ll be able to jump back and forth between the standard wic peer counselor platform and your own state or local content as needed it s easy to do here s how create a folder called statelocal and place it on your desktop name your state or local specific slide show  statelocalpptx  for the links to work you cannot rename these and your presentation must remain within the statelocal folder on your desktop to access the presentation from the main peer counselor platform simply click the state local button on the dashboard when you scroll past the last slide it will automatically return to the dashboard on the main peer counselor platform watch webinar 1a for stepbystep instructions for linking statespecific information to the platform  tips for personalizing your training platform  ',0),(58,'node',' photo credits permissions for images used in the peer counseling training platform photo credits permissions for images used in the peer counseling training platform if you are interested in using any of the images from the peer counseling training platform please view the documents below to find out about the photo credits permissions to extract images from the platform follow these steps  1 in my computer browse to and open the wic pc curriculum folder 2 open the wic pc platform folder 3 open the folder for the module you want to look it then open the powerpoint file that is associated with the image 4 locate the image in the slides right click on the image and save it to your computer photo credits permission information   pdf  module 1 module 2 module 3 module 4 module 5 module 6 module 7 module 8 module 9 module 10 module 11 module 12 module 13  photo credits permissions for images used the peer counseling training platform  ',0),(59,'node',' podcasts for peer counselors podcasts have been created to supplement the peer counselor training experience and can be used to reinforce key messages in the curriculum as part of the initial training monthly peer counselor staff meetings or for peer counselors to download to mobile devices the podcasts are available as part of the presentation platform but are available for easy access here talking with moms using openended questions  wmv mp4 mp3 talking with moms affirmation  wmv mp4 mp3 talking with moms in tough situations  wmv mp4 mp3 helping moms make their infant feeding decision  wmv mp4 mp3 talking with moms who are returning to work  wmv mp4 mp3 how the breast makes milk  wmv mp4 mp3 power of skintoskin contact  wmv mp4 mp3 helping baby attach properly  wmv mp4 mp3 understanding baby talk  wmv mp4 mp3 helping moms breastfeeding exclusively  wmv mp4 mp3 when breastfeeding doesn t go as planned  wmv mp4 mp3 breastfeeding beyond the first month  wmv mp4 mp3  podcasts for peer counselors  ',0),(61,'node',' banner widget to include this banner widget on your web page please copy and paste the following html iframe frameborder  src  https s3amazonawscom brushartwic lovingsupport indexhtml  style height 508px width 217px iframe  campaign materials ',0);
